  ### Comparison with fzf
  
  [Permalink: Comparison with fzf](https://github.com/helix-editor/nucleo#comparison-with-fzf)
  
  For example in the following two screencasts the pattern `///.` is pasted into `fzf` and `nucleo` (both with about 3 million items open).
  
  `fzf` takes a while to filter the text (about 1 second) while `nucleo` has barely any noticeable delay (a single frame in the screencast so about 1/30 seconds). This comparison was made on a very beefy CPU (Ryzen 5950x) so on slower systems the difference may be larger:
  
  [![asciicast](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/693840b0d07a0673db1521a2bc60df13e0043611f93e6562390052990df60386/68747470733a2f2f61736369696e656d612e6f72672f612f3630303531372e737667)](https://asciinema.org/a/600517)[![asciicast](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/22d60c55e0500e635648cba6880a8a52ac5babee483ac37f12a3ef14d6897531/68747470733a2f2f61736369696e656d612e6f72672f612f3630303531362e737667)](https://asciinema.org/a/600516)
  
